Knockinaam Lodge.label: Knockinaam Lodge
Knockinaam Lodge.description: Knockinaam Lodge is a restaurant located in Portpatrick, Dumfries & Galloway, Scotland. As of 2008, the restaurant holds one star in the Michelin Guide. Wikipedia

Quo Vadis (restaurant).label: Quo Vadis
Quo Vadis (restaurant).description: Quo Vadis is a restaurant and private club in Soho, London. It primarily serves modern British food. Wikipedia

Stewart's Restaurants.label: Stewart's Restaurants
Stewart's Restaurants.description: Stewart's Restaurants are classic 1950s style fast-food restaurants located throughout the United States. Restaurants are branded as Stewart's Root Beer or Stewart's Drive-In or similar variations. Wikipedia

The Crab Cooker.label: The Crab Cooker
The Crab Cooker.description: The Crab Cooker is a popular Southern California restaurant specializing in seafood, located on the Balboa Peninsula in Newport Beach, California. Wikipedia

The Old Bull and Bush.label: The Old Bull and Bush
The Old Bull and Bush.description: The Old Bull and Bush is a Grade II listed public house near Hampstead Heath in London which gave its name to the music hall song "Down at the old Bull and Bush" sung by Florrie Forde. Wikipedia

Voodoo Doughnut.label: Voodoo Doughnut
Voodoo Doughnut.description: Voodoo Doughnut is an independent doughnut shop based in Portland, Oregon, known for its unusual doughnuts, eclectic decor, and iconic pink boxes featuring the company logo and illustrations of voodoo priests. Wikipedia

Anchor Inn (Wheaton, Maryland).label: Anchor Inn
Anchor Inn (Wheaton, Maryland).description: The Anchor Inn was a landmark restaurant opened in 1954 in the heart of Wheaton, Maryland located at the corner of University Boulevard West and Georgia Avenue. Wikipedia

L'Atelier de Joël Robuchon (London).label: L'Atelier de Joël Robuchon
L'Atelier de Joël Robuchon (London).description: L'Atelier de Joël Robuchon is a Michelin-starred restaurant in Covent Garden, in the City of Westminster, London. Wikipedia

't Brouwerskolkje.label: 't Brouwerskolkje
't Brouwerskolkje.description: 't Brouwerskolkje was a restaurant located in Overveen, Netherlands. It was a fine dining restaurant that was awarded one Michelin star in the period 2006-2008 and two Michelin stars in the period 2009–2012. Wikipedia

't Misverstant.label: 't Misverstant
't Misverstant.description:
Restaurant 't Misverstant is a restaurant located in Den Bosch, Netherlands. It was a fine dining restaurant that was awarded one Michelin star in the period 1984-1995.
Gault Millau awarded the restaurant 14 out of 20 points. Wikipedia

36 on the Quay.label: 36 on the Quay
36 on the Quay.description: 36 on the Quay is a restaurant located in Emsworth, Hampshire, England. As of 2008, the restaurant holds one star in the Michelin Guide. Wikipedia

Beyti (Istanbul).label: Beyti
Beyti (Istanbul).description: Beyti is a restaurant in Istanbul, Turkey specialising in roasted meat. It was founded in 1945 in Küçükçekmece and has been situated since 1983 in Florya. Wikipedia

Ballymaloe House.label: Ballymaloe House
Ballymaloe House.description: Restaurant The Yeat's Room of Ballymaloe House is a restaurant located in Shanagarry in County Cork, Ireland. It is a fine dining restaurant that was awarded one Michelin star in the period 1975-1980. Wikipedia

Beaulieu, Doorwerth Castle.label: Beaulieu, Doorwerth Castle
Beaulieu, Doorwerth Castle.description:
Restaurant Beaulieu in Doorwerth Castle is a former restaurant located in Doorwerth, in the Netherlands. It was a fine dining restaurant that was awarded one Michelin star in the period 1966-1973 and 1976-1979.
In the first star period G.H. Wikipedia

Beardslee Castle.label: Beardslee Castle
Beardslee Castle.description: Beardslee Castle is a castle in Little Falls, New York, USA, constructed in 1860 as a replica of an Irish castle, and currently used as a restaurant. Wikipedia

Beigel Bake.label: Beigel Bake
Beigel Bake.description: Beigel Bake is a 24-hour bakery on Brick Lane, in London, England. Its menu is focused on bagels, baked in the traditional Jewish style with fillings such as hot salt beef with mustard, chopped herring, and cream cheese and salmon. Wikipedia

Black Cat Bar.label: Black Cat Bar
Black Cat Bar.description: The Black Cat Bar or Black Cat Café was a bar in San Francisco, California. It originally opened in 1906 and closed in 1921. The Black Cat re-opened in 1933 and operated for another 30 years. Wikipedia

Buddy's Pizza.label: Buddy's Pizza
Buddy's Pizza.description: Buddy's Pizza is a pizza restaurant chain based in Detroit, Michigan. Founded in 1946, the chain has an annual revenue of US $20 million. The chain's nine restaurants have a total of 400 employees. Wikipedia

Café Coco.label: Café Coco
Café Coco.description: Café Coco is a 24-hour cafe located at 210 Louise Avenue in Nashville, Tennessee. During the day it is primarily a coffee shop, and at night it has live music, poetry, and comedy. Wikipedia

Carl's Ice Cream.label: Carl's Ice Cream
Carl's Ice Cream.description: Carl's Ice Cream is a roadside ice cream stand located at 2200 Princess Anne Street, Fredericksburg, Virginia. Since 2005, the stand, with its Art Moderne architectural facade, has been listed on the National Register of Historic Places. Wikipedia

Champany Inn.label: Champany Inn
Champany Inn.description: Champany Inn is a restaurant located in Champany, a hamlet on the junctions of the A904 and A803 roads near Linlithgow, West Lothian, Scotland. As of 2008, the restaurant holds one star in the Michelin Guide. Wikipedia

Chez Melange.label: Chez Melange
Chez Melange.description:
Chez Melange is an upscale restaurant and gastropub located in Redondo Beach, California.
It was opened in 1982 by owners Michael Franks and Robert Bell in its original location at the Palos Verdes Inn on Pacific Coast Highway in Redondo Beach. Wikipedia

Château Neercanne.label: Château Neercanne
Château Neercanne.description:
Château Neercanne is a restaurant located in Maastricht in the Netherlands. It is a fine dining restaurant that is awarded one or two Michelin stars in the periods 1957-1982 and 1986–present.
GaultMillau awarded them 15.0 points. Wikipedia
